To this animated picture from Virgil, here is a pendant from Horace, distinctly and spiritedly done with a few vivid touches.

Ep. 11. 39—44. Quod si pudica mulier in partem juvet Domum atque dulces liberos, (Sabina qualis, aut perusta solibus Pernicis uxor Appuli‚) Sacrum et vetustis exstruat lignis focum Lassi sub adventum viri.
